glosses: to vagabond, sleep around, gad, horse around, wander about aimlessly

etymology:
From Ottoman Turkish سورتمك (sürtmek, “to rub grindingly against”), from Proto-Turkic *sür(-t)- (“to rub, smear”). Cognate to sürmek (“to rub, smear, spread”), see further cognates there.
Cognates
Cognate with Old Uyghur [script needed] (sürt-, “to rub”), Karakhanid [script needed] (sürtmēk, “to smear, rub, polish, clean”), Azerbaijani sürtmək (“to rub, polish”), Bashkir һөртөү (hörtöw, “to smear”), Chagatai [script needed] (sürtmek, “to rub”), Kazakh сүрту (sürtu, “to wipe, rub off”), Khakas сӱртерге (sürterge, “to smear, spread, rub”), Kipchak [Arabic needed] (sürüt-, “to erase”), Kyrgyz сүртүү (sürtüü, “to rub, wipe”), Southern Altai сӱртер (sürter, “to smear, spread”), Tatar сөртү (sörtü, “to wipe, smear”), Turkmen sürtmek (“to rub”), Uyghur سۈرتمەك (sürtmek, “to wipe, scrub”), Uzbek surtmoq (“to wipe, polish”).
